FBIS4-38570 "drsov105_p_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Armenian Defense Ministry Denies Attack Armenian Defense Ministry Denies Attack NC3105204894 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network in Armenian 1950 GMT 31 May 94 NC3105204894 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network in Armenian 1950 GMT 31 May 94 Armenian BFN [Text] The Azerbaijani Defense Ministry and [words indistinct] news agencies have distributed yet more misinformation on the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict. According to these reports, an allegedly 500-strong Armenian unit, covered by artillery barrage and supported by armored vehicles and tanks, invaded and advanced 5 kilometers into Azerbaijani territory and occupied a strategically important hill. The Armenian Defense Ministry Press Service said that the misinformation on an Armenian attack on Nakhichevan is mere calumny, the entire responsibility for which rests with the Azerbaijani Defense [words indistinct].
